<br>
There is no doubt in my mind that item decay is intended to reduce the feasiblity of twinking, and as far as it goes that is all to the good. Twinking has seriously distorted the development of EQ and it is almost inconceivable that Verant would develop EQ 2 without addressing this issue. <br>
<br>
I don't think you need fear losing valuable, hard to replace items to decay. One of the benefits of decay is that it will reduce the need for long camps without risk of saturating the server economy with items. This is a necessary departure from the &quot;Evercamp&quot; model in order to increase the game's appeal to casual players, a market segment Verant and SoE dare not neglect now that EQ is no longer virtually the only game in town. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utaliewin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taliewin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 319<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/23/02 8:20:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16068.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thoughts on EQ2</span><hr size=1> Item decay, no set spawns, no repopping of named (in other words, they really die), no set classes (character can learn any skill), dynamic quests (not the DAoC kind)...are the MMORPG of the future, so I can see why VI want to go that way. In fact VI falls short by a long way compared to some other games in development at the moment in regards to these 'realistic features'.<br>
<br>
Personally I think it is a turn for the better. Items will no longer be the focus. I think a lot of gamers are getting burnt out by item acquisition now as well, there is only so many items that one can think of, only so many stats that one can attain before there is no further to go, no challenge. <br>
<br>
Welcome to the new challenge: Character Character Development (My own phrase). You don't develop your character's stats or gear, you develop their character! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
But to the topic at hand: I did hear at one point that there would be no transferring of anything between the two games, but that was a while ago and they may have changed their minds. Personally I can see that they would allow it, IF the work involved wasn't so huge (how many items will they have to keep track of being brought across, and can they make it auto-matic or will the two games be totally different file systems).<br>
<br>
